description.plain:
Internet Money is a Los Angeles-based music production collective and label founded by Taz Taylor. Members of the collective have produced for some of rap’s biggest names, including Drake, Juice WRLD, Trippie Redd, Lil Uzi Vert, XXXTENTACION, and many more.

The production members also run a YouTube channel by the same name, Internet Money, where they post beat-making videos, tracks, and general tips.

In October 2019, Internet Money signed a joint venture deal with TenThousand Projects, which now releases music for all of Internet Money’s artists. The first song released under this deal was “Somebody” with Lil Tecca and A Boogie wit da Hoodie, released October 11, 2019.

description.plain:
On “His & Hers,” Internet Money producers reunite with Don Toliver and Gunna after collaborating on the summer 2020 hit “Lemonade”. This time around joined by Lil Uzi Vert, the artists deliver catchy melodies over an IM-produced beat.

Mainly conducted by IM founder Taz Taylor and video director Cole Bennett, the teasing of the track began on April 1, 2021, with Taz Taylor’s announcement of the collaboration. After the leak of a demo and several delays, Taz finally announced the song’s release on May 13, 2021.

Just like “Lemonade,” the release of “His & Hers” was followed by the premiere of a Lyrical Lemonade music video, giving more exposure to the song.

description.plain:
“Lost Me” is a collaborative release from artists Lil Mosey, iann dior and Lil Skies. On the track, the trio boast about their luxurious lifestyles; an influx in currency, exotic sport vehicles and excessive use in narcotics.

The original title of the track was “Kobe”, however the professional basketball player Kobe Bryant passed away due to an accidental helicopter crash on January 26, 2020. Out of respect, Taz Taylor later changed the track’s original title from “Kobe” to “Lost Me”.

Due to a problem with the artists and record labels in early 2020, the track was originally scrapped from the album as Taz Taylor explained in a tweet.

On April 21, 2020, all of the artists and labels reunited as iann dior confirmed the track was releasing soon. The track was confirmed to be featured on the collective Internet Money album, B4THESTORM.

After much long-awaited anticipation, the track was finally released on August 27, 2020, along with a lyric video.

description.plain:
On “Speak,” The Kid LAROI details his relationship issues with women, mentioning how he has lost all of his patience. He also alludes to his rock-star lifestyle and his aspirations.

The song is featured on Internet Money’s debut collective album B4 THE STORM.
